Render → New Web Service → connect repo

Root Directory: (leave blank if app.py is at repo root; set to "backend" if inside /backend)

Build Command:
pip install -r requirements.txt && python -c "import app; app._maybe_init()"

Start Command:
gunicorn -w 2 -b 0.0.0.0:$PORT app:app

Environment:
FRONTEND_ORIGIN = https://www.sreesasthapowersolutions.com
# or
ALLOWED_ORIGINS = https://www.sreesasthapowersolutions.com, https://sriaparna70-maker.github.io

ZOHO_EMAIL = sivaramanganesan@zohomail.in
ZOHO_APP_PASSWORD = <your 16-char Zoho app password>
ZOHO_TO_EMAIL = sivaramanganesan@zohomail.in
ZOHO_SMTP_HOST = smtp.zoho.in
ZOHO_SMTP_PORT = 465

# Optional (attach a Disk and set for persistence)
# DATA_DIR = /data

Health:
GET /api/health  -> {"ok": true, ...}

Forms:
POST /api/contact    -> {name, email, message}
POST /api/openaccess -> {name, email, phone, sanctioned_load, monthly_kwh, callback?, eb_bill?}

eb_bill (optional):
{"filename":"bill.pdf","content_type":"application/pdf","b64":"<base64-data>"}
